# Backend

- AlignEd is anonymous: there are exactly two write paths — the insert-only
  anonymous `assessments` row on quiz completion, and the `send-results`
  Supabase Edge Function (Resend email). Do not add others without PRD change.
- Validate every input with zod at the boundary before any DB call.
- Return the canonical shape: { data, error, meta }. On failure set data null
  and error { code, message }; never leak stack traces or secrets.
- Reference data (courses, careers) is public-read via the anon client and
  rendered on the server; program ranking goes through the `match_courses`
  RPC — never re-implement its logic in TypeScript.
- The service-role key exists only inside Edge Functions; it must never appear
  in Next.js code, client or server.
- Enforce access rules in the database via RLS (public read on reference
  tables, insert-only on `assessments`, no read-back); treat server checks as
  defense in depth, not the only gate.
- Wrap DB and network calls in try/catch with explicit error types; log with
  context, never raw emails or secrets.
- The email path is send-and-discard: raw addresses are never persisted — only
  a salted hash for rate limiting. Rate-limit per IP and per hashed email;
  keep the honeypot check.
- Completion-insert failures must never block results (they render
  client-side); retry the insert in the background.
- Keep handlers small; push reusable logic into `src/lib/` helpers.
